<item>
            <title>[LU-18952] convert lustre/tests/mmap_sanity.c over to use llapi_test_util.c</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18952</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The test selection code in &lt;tt&gt;mmap_sanity.c&lt;/tt&gt; could be modified to share the new test selection infrastructure added in &lt;tt&gt;llapi_test_util.c&lt;/tt&gt; from patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/58786&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/58786&lt;/a&gt; (&quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15762&quot; title=&quot;Interop: sanity-hsm test_500: mdt_coordinator.c:1629:mdt_hsm_update_request_state()) lustre-MDT0000: Cannot find running request for cookie 0x624a1c9f on fid=[0x2000088da:0xe2:0x0]&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-15762&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-15762&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; tests: skip llapi_hsm_test113 on old server&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Some small changes would be needed in &lt;tt&gt;llapi_test_util.c&lt;/tt&gt; to pass the Lustre mountpoint as an argument to the test function (as &lt;tt&gt;mmap_sanity.c&lt;/tt&gt; does) instead of accessing it via a global variable, but this seems like a net improvement.  Other than this, the code seems fairly similar (except to allow &lt;tt&gt;&amp;#45;e&lt;/tt&gt; as an alias of &lt;tt&gt;&amp;#45;s&lt;/tt&gt;) and looks like it could easily be shared.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
